      "content": "You need to adjust your definition of \"sophistication\" to fit the local context, which means respecting the established norms of the region you are in. In places where Western suits are out of place, adopting high-quality, locally appropriate attire shows respect and understanding. For instance, in some parts of Asia, immaculate traditional wear or very modest, high-quality fabrics are the true markers of professionalism. Ultimately, looking polished means looking like you belong and respect the local customs, not just wearing a suit.",
